#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_spatial.rst:195
msgid ""
"**Note:** In the mathematical sense, rotation is a matrix and not a "
"vector. The three Euler angles, which are the three independent "
"parameters of the Euler-angle parametrization of the rotation matrix, are"
" stored in a :ref:`Vector3 <class_Vector3>` data structure not because "
"the rotation is a vector, but only because :ref:`Vector3 <class_Vector3>`"
" exists as a convenient data-structure to store 3 floating-point numbers."
" Therefore, applying affine operations on the rotation \"vector\" is not "
"meaningful."
